casebody.data:
HERMAN M. DIAMOND, PLAINTIFF-PROSECUTOR, v. GUSTAV BACH, COUNTY CLERK, ET AL., DEFENDANTS-RESPONDENTS. Argued June 18, 1931 Decided May 16, 1932.

Before Justices Trenchard and Donges.

Tor the prosecutor, John Warren. Tor the respondents, Herbert Ciarle Gilson. Per Curiam.

Application is made for a writ of certiorari to review a judgment entered in the District Court of the Tirst Judicial District of Hudson County, which judgment was subsequently docketed in the Hudson County Circuit Court.

A writ of certiorari was granted applicant on September 1st, 19.22, which was in 1926 dismissed for lack of prosecution.

*777In view of the circumstances of the case, as presented to us, we are constrained to deny the application for a writ of certiorari.

The application is denied, with costs.
